## Architecture Overview

- View layer (`views`): shows the pages and loads JS/CSS libraries.
- Client service layer (`scripts/Service.js`): sends AJAX requests with specific POST keys.
- Controller layer (`controllers/UserController.php`): checks POST keys and calls the right method.
- Business layer (`bl/UserManagement.php`): contains main app logic.
- Model layer (`model`): handles database connection and SQL queries.

## Request Routing Map

| POST Keys | Routed Method | Storage Path |
|---|---|---|
| `fname`, `lName` | `addUserFunc()` | Database (`tbl_registration`) |
| `uFName`, `uLName`, `uID` | `updateUserFunc()` | Session |
| `dID` | `deleteUserFunc()` | Session |
| `lFName`, `lLName` | `loginUserFunc()` | Session |

## Key Files and Responsibilities

### `bl/UserManagement.php`

Core business logic class.

| Method | Parameters | Simple Description |
|---|---|---|
| `__construct()` | None | Creates a `Database` object, opens PDO connection, and creates a `Registration` model instance. |
| `addUserFunc()` | `$firstName`, `$lastName` | Calls `createRegistration()` to insert a new user into MySQL. |
| `updateUserFunc()` | `$firstName`, `$lastName`, `$userID` | Updates a user in the session array using the given index. |
| `deleteUserFunc()` | `$userID` | Deletes a user from the session array and reindexes the array. |
| `getUser()` | None | Returns users from the session array for table display. |
| `loginUserFunc()` | `$firstName`, `$lastName` | Checks first name and last name against session data, then returns `true` or `false`. |

### `model/database.php`

PDO connection factory.

- Host: `localhost`
- Port: `3307`
- Database: `projectappdev_db`
- Username: `root`
- Password: empty

Returns a PDO connection with `PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION` enabled.

### `model/registrationModel.php`

Registration data model.

| Method | Parameters | Simple Description |
|---|---|---|
| `__construct()` | `$db` | Saves the PDO connection in a private class property. |
| `createRegistration()` | `$firstName`, `$lastName` | Runs a prepared `INSERT` query into `tbl_registration` using bound parameters and timestamps. |

### `controllers/UserController.php`

Entry point for AJAX POST operations.

What it does:
- starts the session,
- creates `UserManagement`,
- checks which POST keys were sent,
- calls the matching method.

### `scripts/Service.js`

Front-end service functions:

| Function | Parameters | Simple Description |
|---|---|---|
| `addFunc()` | None | Gets first/last name from form and sends POST to add a user. |
| `updateFunc()` | `userID` | Sends POST request to update the selected user. |
| `deleteFunc()` | `userID` | Sends POST request to delete the selected user. |
| `changeFirstName()` | None | Legacy function; overlaps with add behavior. |
| `redirectFunc()` | `redirectID` | Redirects to Login, Dashboard, or Registration page. |
| `loginFunc()` | None | Sends login POST request and handles success/failure feedback. |

### `views/RegistrationPage.php`

Main screen that contains:

- Registration form
- Login button
- DataTables-enhanced table (`#myTable`)

Also includes jQuery, SweetAlert2, Materialize, Material Icons, and DataTables CDN assets.

## Database Notes

The current insert query expects a table named `tbl_registration` and writes these columns:

- `firstName`
- `lastName`
- `createdAt`
- `updatedAt`

If your schema includes additional non-null columns with no defaults, INSERT will fail unless those columns are handled.

## Setup

### Prerequisites

- XAMPP (Apache + MySQL)
- PHP with PDO MySQL enabled (`pdo_mysql`)
- MySQL database `projectappdev_db`

### Local Configuration

1. Place the project in your XAMPP htdocs directory.
2. Ensure Apache is running.
3. Ensure the correct MySQL instance is running on port `3307`.
4. Verify database credentials in `model/database.php`.

### Run

Open the app in browser via your XAMPP host path to `views/RegistrationPage.php`.

